dct_title_s: Regnorum Castellæ novæ, Andalusiæ, Granadæ, Valentiæ, et Murciæ, in episcopatus etc. divisorum
dct_description_sm: Map of southern Spain. Relief shown pictorially. "Cum priv. potentiss D. D. ordinum Hollandiæ et Westfrisiæ." "In 1688 de Wit obtained a privilege from the States General to publish his maps; atlases published after this date carry the marking "cum privilegio" ... In 1710 de Wit's stock was dispersed and sold ... "--Tooley's dictionary of mapmakers.
